
To split a PDF file into smaller PDFs based on the desired number of pages using C++, you can utilize the PoDoFo library. PoDoFo is a powerful library for handling PDF files in C++. Below is a simple implementation:

Prerequisites
Install the PoDoFo library:

On Linux: Run sudo apt-get install libpodofo-dev.
On Windows: Download and compile PoDoFo from its official GitHub repository.
Set up your C++ development environment to include the PoDoFo headers and link against the PoDoFo library.

